16 AUTHOR: Add the following Senate Coauthor: Pederson
17 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Page 1, strike the stricken title, enacting clause
and entire bill and insert
18
19 “An Act relating to schools; directing the State
Department of Education, in certain consultation, to
20 establish the Binocular Vision Screening Program as a
two-year pilot program; directing the program to
21 offer vision screenings to students in kindergarten,
first, and third grades; defining term; requiring
22 schools to provide certain screening within certain
number of days beginning in certain school year;
23 requiring screenings to be performed by certain
personnel; clarifying certain requirement; directing
24 the Department to electronically submit certain
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3016 Page 1

1 report by certain date and post it on its website;
creating the Binocular Screening Revolving Fund;
2 specifying source of fund; providing for
expenditures; providing purpose of fund; providing
3 for codification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
4
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
6 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1210.286 of Title 70, unless
8 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 A. The State Department of Education, in consultation with the
10 State Department of Health, shall establish a two-year pilot program
11 known as the Binocular Vision Screening Program for schools to offer
12 vision screenings to students in kindergarten and first and third
13 grades that are designed to identify convergence insufficiency.
14 “Convergence insufficiency” means a vision disorder characterized by
15 a decreased ability to converge the eyes and maintain binocular
16 fusion while focusing on a near target.
17 B. Beginning with the 2026-2027 school year, the program shall
18 require schools to provide all students in kindergarten and first
19 and third grades with a comprehensive binocular vision screening
20 within ninety (90) days of the start of the school year.
21 C. The screening required by subsection B of this section shall
22 be performed by personnel listed on the statewide registry
23 maintained by the State Department of Health pursuant to Section
24 1210.284 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3016 Page 2

1 D. The screenings required by this section shall be in addition
2 to the screenings required in Section 1210.284 of Title 70 of the
3 Oklahoma Statutes.
4 E. The State Department of Education shall electronically
5 submit a report on the Binocular Vision Screening Program including
6 any legislative recommendations to the Governor, the President Pro
7 Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker of the House of
8 Representatives by November 1, 2028. The Department shall post the
9 report on its website.
10 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1210.287 of Title 70, unless
12 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
14 fund for the State Department of Education to be designated the
15 “Binocular Screening Revolving Fund”. The fund shall be a
16 continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall
17 consist of all monies received by the State Department of Education
18 from monies appropriated or apportioned by the Legislature for the
19 purpose of implementing the provisions of Section 1 of this act.
20 All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
21 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the State
22 Department of Education for the purpose of establishing and
23 maintaining the Binocular Vision Screening Program created in
24 Section 1 of this act. Monies in the Binocular Screening Revolving
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3016 Page 3

1 Fund shall supplement and not supplant existing school vision
2 screening funding.
3 B. Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon warrants
4 issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by
5 law with the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
6 Services for approval and payment.
7 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
8 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
9 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
10 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
11 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.”
12 Passed the Senate the 23rd day of April, 2026.
