18 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1210.286 of Title 70, unless
20 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 A. The State Department of Education, in consultation with the
22 State Department of Health, shall establish a two-year pilot program
23 known as the Binocular Vision Screening Program, for schools to
24 offer vision screenings to students in kindergarten, first, and
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3016 Page 1

1 thir d grades that are designed to identify convergence insufficiency
2 disorders. "Convergence insufficiency" means a vision disorder
3 characterized by a decreased ability to converge the eyes and
4 maintain binocular fusion while focusing on a near target.
5 B. Beginning with the 2026-2027 school year, the program shall
6 require schools to provide all students in kindergarten, first, and
7 third grades with a comprehensive binocular vision screening within
8 thirty (30) days of the start of the school year.
9 C. The screening required in subsection B of this section shall
10 be performed by school nurses, vision therapists, or optometric
11 technicians who are specifically trained to administer and interpret
12 results of a comprehensive binocular screening.
13 D. The screenings required by this section shall be in addition
14 to the screenings required in Section 5-148.2 of Title 70 of the
15 Oklahoma Statutes.
16 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1210.287 of Title 70, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
20 fund for the State Department of Education to be designated the
21 "Binocular Screening Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a
22 continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall
23 consist of all monies received by the State Department of Education
24 from monies appropriated or apportioned by the Legislature. All
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3016 Page 2

1 moni es accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby appropriated
2 and may be budgeted and expended by the State Department of
3 Education for the purpose of establishing and maintaining the
4 program created in Section 1 of this act. Monies in the Binocular
5 Screening Revolving Fund shall supplement and not supplant existing
6 school vision screening funding.
7 B. Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon warrants
8 issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by
9 law with the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
10 Services for approval and payment.
11 SECTION 7. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
12 Passed the House of Representatives the 25th day of March, 2026.
